http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#com.@value: This ontology aims to model the Occupancy Behavior domain according to the obXML schema (https://behavior.lbl.gov/?q=obXML)
The action the occupant performs to satisfy its need.
Building where the occupancy behaviors occur.
N-ary class to represent the value and the names of coefficients inside mathematical formulas
Circumstances that motivate the occupant behavior.
Class to represent equipments the occupant interact with but do not influence the environment. These systems also contribute in the energy performance analysis.
The Inaction class represents the decision of an occupant to not act and remain uncomfortable within a space
The Interaction class represents the interaction of the occupant with the systems within the space to recover its comfort.

The Report class indicates that an occupant seeks assistance or
files a complaint about their personal discomfort, but does not take
direct action to satisfy their needs.
Class to represent the different spaces the building have and where the occupant behaviors occur.
